{"story": {"id": "consolidation", "title": "The Consolidation \u2014 Fan-In Before Exit", "difficulty": "HARD", "seed_node_id": 30179316, "pattern": "fan_in", "narrative": "This story examines a **consolidation (fan-in)** pattern: transaction 30179316 is an illicit node that receives funds from 177 separate upstream transactions. This massive fan-in is typical of a tumbling service or darknet marketplace wallet that aggregates payments from many sources before forwarding the consolidated balance downstream. The HARD difficulty comes from the volume of incoming edges and the mixed-label nature of predecessors (most are unlabeled / unknown), making it difficult to determine the true source of the illicit funds.\n", "steps": [{"step_num": 1, "title": "The consolidation point", "description": "Transaction 30179316 is flagged as illicit (class = 1) and has an in-degree of 177 \u2014 the highest among illicit fan-in nodes in the dataset. This extreme concentration of incoming edges is a strong structural signal of a consolidation hub.\n", "highlight_nodes": [30179316], "highlight_edges": [], "trace_direction": "upstream"}, {"step_num": 2, "title": "Sample the incoming flow", "description": "Among the 177 predecessors, a sample of 15 are shown. All sampled predecessors are unlabeled (class = 3 / unknown), meaning we cannot easily confirm whether they are part of the laundering chain or coincidental traffic. This label ambiguity is what makes this a HARD case \u2014 the structural pattern is clear but the ML model provides no additional signal.\n", "highlight_nodes": [30179316, 30179589, 30179423, 30180253, 25342845, 30179594, 28921375, 30179593, 30179400], "highlight_edges": [[30179589, 30179316], [30179423, 30179316], [30180253, 30179316], [25342845, 30179316], [30179594, 30179316], [28921375, 30179316], [30179593, 30179316], [30179400, 30179316]], "trace_direction": "upstream"}, {"step_num": 3, "title": "Predecessor diversity", "description": "The 177 predecessors span multiple timestep ranges, suggesting that this consolidation accumulated funds over an extended period. This is consistent with a marketplace escrow or tumbling service that batches many small payments into a single large outbound transaction. The wide predecessor set makes manual tracing impractical without automated clustering.\n", "highlight_nodes": [30179316, 30180257, 30179832, 30179418, 30179376, 30179461, 30179871, 30179386], "highlight_edges": [[30180257, 30179316], [30179832, 30179316], [30179418, 30179316], [30179376, 30179316], [30179461, 30179316], [30179871, 30179316], [30179386, 30179316]], "trace_direction": "upstream"}, {"step_num": 4, "title": "Downstream exit", "description": "After consolidation, the combined funds flow downstream from 30179316. Following this exit edge reveals where the laundered money ultimately goes \u2014 typically toward an exchange, a mixer, or a cash-out node. The downstream trace completes the consolidation story by showing the final destination of aggregated illicit funds.\n", "highlight_nodes": [30179316], "highlight_edges": [], "trace_direction": "downstream"}]}, "nodes": [{"data": {"id": "658042", "label": "658042", "class": 2, "class_label": "licit", "color": "#22c55e", "hop": 1, "timestep": 37}}, {"data": {"id": "4246202", "label": "4246202", "class": 3, "class_label": "unknown", "color": "#6b7280", "hop": 1, "timestep": 37}}, {"data": {"id": "5733497", "label": "5733497", "class": 3, "class_label": "unknown", "color": "#6b7280", "hop": 1, "timestep": 37}}, {"data": {"id": "20219869", "label": "20219869", "class": 3, "class_label": "unknown", "color": "#6b7280", "hop": 1, "timestep": 37}}, {"data": {"id": "21189498", "label": "21189498", "class": 3, "class_label": "unknown", "color": "#6b7280", "hop": 1, "timestep": 37}}, {"data": {"id": "22773369", "label": "22773369", "class": 3, "class_label": "unknown", "color": "#6b7280", "hop": 1, "timestep": 37}}, {"data": {"id": "25342845", "label": "25342845", "class": 3, "cl